</details>

### DESCRIPTION

There are two related issues when using an **Android stylus (like Samsung S-Pen)** with **TextField** and **CupertinoTextField**.

Issue 1 — **Keyboard opens unexpectedly**

When directly scribbling (handwriting) on a TextField or CupertinoTextField using the stylus, the software keyboard opens automatically, even though the expectation is that stylus input should not trigger the keyboard.


Issue 2 — **Scribble input inconsistency**

When using _**keyboardType: TextInputType.none**_, stylus scribble input (handwriting recognition) does not work initially on TextField or CupertinoTextField.

However, if the user first scribbles on another text field that does not have TextInputType.none, then returns to the TextField or CupertinoTextField with TextInputType.none, scribble input starts working there too.

In other words:

Initially, stylus scribble fails on text fields that set keyboardType: TextInputType.none.

After scribbling once in a normal text field (without TextInputType.none), scribble input starts working in all text fields — including those that previously failed.

**This makes stylus-based input inconsistent and unreliable for stylus-driven workflows.**

**_This breaks stylus-based handwriting or form input workflows in Flutter apps.
Apps relying on stylus-only input (without keyboard) cannot provide a consistent user experience._**

### Steps to reproduce
1.Create a new Flutter project and replace main.dart with
2. Run app on samsung tablet with s Pen (My device - Galaxy Tab S9)
3. For first Issue - directly scribble with S-pen on the default textField  (without paass any params) , keyboard was open
4. For Second Issue - First Scribble on with Params of TextInputType.none  in Field , textField was not accepting the scribble input , once scribble on default textField and then try on that , its was accepted the input

### Expected results

The keyboard should not open when writing with a stylus.

Scribble (stylus handwriting recognition) should work consistently regardless of keyboardType

Setting keyboardType: TextInputType.none should suppress the keyboard but still allow stylus input detection.

### Actual results

Keyboard opens even when scribbling with stylus input.

Scribble does not initially work on fields with TextInputType.none.

After scribbling in a normal text field, scribble suddenly starts working in those previously non-functional fields.

### Code sample

